Thus, infections caused by the fungus 
 Candida spp. have been recognized for many years. However, of interest here is the abrupt emergence of a new strain 
 Candida auris which presents a profound puzzle (
 Lockhart et al., 2017). This new strain which is multi-drug resistant has emerged as a major cause of mortality and is posing a serious challenge for health officials the world over (
 Chowdhary, Sharma, & Meis, 2017; 
 Cortegiani et al., 2018; 
 Jeffery-Smith et al., 2018; 
 Lockhart et al., 2017). While 
 Candida auris was reported for the first time in Japan in 2009 it appears to have been 
 isolated more or less simultaneously in many widely separated locations across the world.
